ign=left class=m><span class=title> story continued</span><hr size=1> In one of the darker corners of the inn, a robed figure sat watching the display.  He saw the reaction of the so-called &quot;paladins&quot; when the &quot;dark ones&quot;, as the others called them, walked in.  He had been following them for the last few days trying to find an opportune moment to speak with them and was not about to allow them to come to harm.  Beneath the robes his hands began to glow as he quitely wove a spell.  Nervously his tail twitched beneath his robe and he almost lept from his seat when the bard approached them.  But nothing happened.  The bard embraced the one &quot;dark one&quot; and though everyone seemed surprised, no one made a move against them.  So he quietly sipped his mead and waited for his chance to speak with them.  He hoped that though they be of different race, the fact they worshiped the same gods would be enough to convince them to afford him solace in their city, as well as access to the wealth of dark knowledge that they are rumored to posess.  He had waiting four weeks to find a member of the &quot;dark ones&quot; he could speak to...he was patient enough to wait a little while longer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vanlaan>Vanlaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/4/01 4:34:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: story continued</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> In one of the darker corners of the inn, a robed figure sat watching the display. He saw the reaction of the so-called &quot;paladins&quot; when the &quot;dark ones&quot;, as the 